 Phase 2 — Query, Graph & Daily Notes

 Goal: Query the index by tags/links/frontmatter, export the graph, and manage daily notes.

 2.1 Query engine (core/query.rs, cli/query.rs)

 Syntax for oi query:
 oi query "tag:#rust"                    # notes with tag #rust
 oi query "tag:#rust AND tag:#async"     # intersection
 oi query "link:api-design"             # notes that link to api-design
 oi query "backlink:api-design"         # notes that api-design links to
 oi query "title:auth"                  # title contains "auth"
 oi query "front:status=draft"          # frontmatter field match
 oi query "words>1000"                  # word count filter
 oi query "orphan:true"                 # notes with no inbound or outbound links

 Implementation:
 - Parse query string into a filter AST (keep it simple — no need for a full parser, a basic recursive descent or even split-on-AND/OR is fine for v1)
 - Translate filters to SQL WHERE clauses with JOINs
 - Output: table (default), JSON (--json), or just paths (--paths)

 2.2 Check command (cli/check.rs)

 oi check                    # run all checks
 oi check --orphans          # notes with no links in or out
 oi check --broken-links     # wikilinks pointing to non-existent notes
 oi check --dead-tags        # tags used only once
 - Queries the index for each check type
 - Outputs a report with file paths and line numbers
 - Exit code 1 if any issues found (useful in CI/pre-commit hooks)

 2.3 Graph export (core/graph.rs, cli/graph.rs)

 oi graph                    # full graph as JSON adjacency list
 oi graph --format dot       # Graphviz DOT format
 oi graph --format json      # JSON (default)
 oi graph --filter "tag:#project-x"  # subgraph
 oi graph --depth 2 --root "api-design"  # ego graph, 2 hops from root

 JSON output shape:
 {
   "nodes": [
     { "id": "api-design", "path": "notes/api-design.md", "tags": ["#arch"], "word_count": 450 }
   ],
   "edges": [
     { "source": "api-design", "target": "auth-middleware", "line": 23 }
   ]
 }

 DOT output for piping to dot -Tsvg -o graph.svg.

 2.4 Daily notes (cli/daily.rs)

 oi daily                    # create/print today's note path
 oi daily --open             # create and print path (user pipes to editor)
 oi daily --yesterday
 oi daily --date 2026-03-25
 oi daily --template path/to/template.md
 - Creates {daily_folder}/{daily_format}.md if it doesn't exist
 - If a template is configured, copies template content into new daily note
 - Prints the path to stdout (so users can do nvim $(oi daily))

