 Phase 3 — AI Integration Layer

 Goal: Pluggable AI backend with embedding-based semantic search and LLM-powered commands.

 3.1 Provider traits (ai/provider.rs, ai/embedder.rs)

 #[async_trait]
 pub trait LlmProvider: Send + Sync {
     async fn complete(&self, prompt: &str, system: Option<&str>) -> Result<String>;
     fn name(&self) -> &str;
 }

 #[async_trait]
 pub trait Embedder: Send + Sync {
     async fn embed(&self, texts: &[&str]) -> Result<Vec<Vec<f32>>>;
     fn dimension(&self) -> usize;
     fn model_name(&self) -> &str;
 }

 3.2 Provider implementations (ai/providers/)

 Claude (claude.rs):
 - Uses reqwest to call https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages
 - Reads ANTHROPIC_API_KEY from env
 - Model configurable in config.toml (default: claude-sonnet-4-6)
 - For embeddings: delegate to Voyage AI or fall back to OpenAI embeddings (Claude doesn't have a native embedding API — document this clearly)

 OpenAI-compatible (openai.rs):
 - Calls /v1/chat/completions and /v1/embeddings
 - Reads OPENAI_API_KEY from env
 - base_url configurable (so it works with any OpenAI-compatible API)

 Ollama (ollama.rs):
 - Calls local Ollama REST API (/api/generate, /api/embeddings)
 - Default URL http://localhost:11434, configurable
 - No API key needed

 Provider factory:
 - Read ai.provider from config, return the right Box<dyn LlmProvider> + Box<dyn Embedder>
 - Config:
 [ai]
 provider = "claude"          # claude | openai | ollama
 model = "claude-sonnet-4-6"  # LLM model for completions
 embedding_provider = "openai"  # can differ from completion provider
 embedding_model = "text-embedding-3-small"
 # base_url = "https://api.openai.com/v1"   # for openai-compatible
 # ollama_url = "http://localhost:11434"

 3.3 Embedding indexer (ai/semantic.rs)

 oi ai index                 # embed all notes, store in SQLite
 oi ai index --force         # re-embed everything

 - Chunk notes into ~500 token segments (split on headings or paragraphs)
 - Batch embed chunks (respect rate limits — configurable batch size)
 - Store embeddings as BLOB (f32 bytes) in embeddings table
 - Incremental: skip notes whose content_hash hasn't changed

 Vector search (no external vector DB needed for v1):
 - Load relevant embeddings from SQLite
 - Compute cosine similarity in Rust (it's fast enough for <50k chunks)
 - Return top-K results
 - Future optimization: add HNSW index via usearch crate if needed

 3.4 AI commands (ai/commands.rs, cli/ai.rs)

 # Semantic search over notes
 oi ai search "authentication patterns"
 # → Returns top 5 notes with relevance scores and excerpts

 # Ask a question, grounded in your notes
 oi ai ask "What are our conventions for error handling?"
 # → LLM answers using retrieved note context (RAG)

 # Suggest connections between a note and the rest of the vault
 oi ai connect api-design
 # → "api-design.md could link to: error-handling.md (both discuss middleware),
 #    auth-patterns.md (shared context on request lifecycle)"

 # Summarize a set of notes
 oi ai summarize --tag "#meeting-notes"
 # → Generates a summary across all matching notes

 # Generate a draft note from context
 oi ai draft "Compare our auth approaches" --context "#auth"
 # → Creates a new .md file with AI-generated content, linked to source notes

 RAG implementation (ai/context.rs):
 1. For ask/draft: embed the query → vector search → retrieve top-K chunks
 2. Assemble a prompt with the retrieved chunks as context
 3. System prompt instructs the LLM to only use provided context, cite sources by note title
 4. Return the response with source attribution

 3.5 Config for AI (config.toml additions)

 [ai]
 provider = "claude"
 model = "claude-sonnet-4-6"
 embedding_provider = "openai"
 embedding_model = "text-embedding-3-small"
 chunk_size = 500           # tokens per chunk
 search_top_k = 10          # default results for semantic search
 context_top_k = 5          # chunks to include in RAG context
 batch_size = 50            # embeddings per API call

