 ---
 Key Design Decisions

 1. SQLite over in-memory index — Persists between runs, enables incremental indexing, fast enough for 100k+ notes. No external database to manage.
 2. No custom vector DB — Cosine similarity in Rust over SQLite-stored vectors is fast enough for vaults up to ~50k chunks. HNSW can be added later if needed via the usearch crate.
 3. Pluggable AI from day one — The trait abstraction is minimal overhead and avoids a painful refactor later. Claude as default, OpenAI-compatible for flexibility, Ollama for
 local/private use.
 4. Embedding provider separate from completion provider — Users may want Claude for completions but OpenAI for embeddings (since Claude doesn't have a native embedding API). Config
 supports this.
 5. CLI binary name: oi — Short, fast to type, stands for OpenIdiom. Configured via [[bin]] in Cargo.toml.
 6. No watch mode in v1 — oi index is explicit. A --watch flag can be added later using notify crate. Keep it simple.
 7. Obsidian-compatible — Reads standard [[wikilinks]], #tags, and YAML frontmatter. Users can run OpenIdiom alongside Obsidian on the same vault. The .openidiom/ folder is
 self-contained.
